ADMIN PANEL UI FLOW SPEC

Tech constraints

Ionic Framework (latest)

Angular v16+

Standalone components only

No NgModules

Use Angular Signals for state management

Use input() signal inputs, not @Input()

Use effect() and computed() where appropriate

Routing via standalone provideRouter

Forms via ReactiveFormsModule (standalone import)

1. Application Structure
Root layout

App uses a split-pane layout:

Left: Admin sidebar navigation

Right: Routed content outlet

Required root components

AppComponent (standalone)

AdminLayoutComponent (shell for all admin routes)

2. Routing Structure (Standalone)

Define routes using provideRouter.

/admin
  ├── dashboard
  ├── elections
  │     ├── list
  │     └── create
  ├── candidates
  ├── voters
  ├── voting-control
  ├── results
  └── audit-logs


All routes under /admin use AdminLayoutComponent as the parent.

3. AdminLayoutComponent
Responsibilities

Persistent sidebar

Top header with admin info and logout button

<ion-router-outlet> for child views

Sidebar navigation items

Dashboard

Elections

Candidates

Voters

Voting Control

Results

Audit Logs

Behavior

Highlight active route

Sidebar collapses on small screens

4. Dashboard Component
Component

AdminDashboardComponent

UI sections

Stats cards

Total voters

Total candidates

Total votes cast

Election status

System alerts panel

Warnings or system messages

Data handling

Use signals for dashboard state

Use computed() for derived values

Read-only UI, no mutations here

5. Election Management
Components

ElectionListComponent

ElectionCreateComponent

ElectionListComponent
UI

Table or list of elections

Columns:

Election name

Status (Draft / Active / Ended)

Start date

End date

Action buttons:

View

Edit (disabled if election is active or ended)

Behavior

Clicking "Create Election" navigates to /admin/elections/create

ElectionCreateComponent
UI

Reactive form with:

Election name

Description

Start datetime

End datetime

Submit button

Cancel button

Validation rules

Start date must be before end date

All fields required

Data flow

Form state managed via signals

On submit:

Call service

Navigate back to election list

6. Candidate Management
Component

CandidateManagementComponent

UI

Candidate list with:

Name

Party/Group

Assigned election

Actions:

Add candidate

Edit candidate

Delete candidate (disabled if election is active)

Add/Edit Modal

Use Ionic modal

Reactive form

Submit and cancel actions

7. Voter Management
Component

VoterManagementComponent

UI

Table of voters

Columns:

Name

Email / ID

Voting status

Account status

Actions:

Activate / Deactivate

Reset credentials

Optional

CSV upload button for bulk voter creation

8. Voting Control
Component

VotingControlComponent

UI

Current election status indicator

Control buttons:

Start voting

Pause voting

End voting

Behavior

Buttons enabled/disabled based on election state

Confirmation dialog before state changes

9. Results View
Component

ResultsComponent

UI

Candidate-wise vote counts

Percentage bars or charts

Export buttons:

Export CSV

Export PDF

Rules

Results only visible when election status is Ended

Disable UI otherwise

10. Audit Logs
Component

AuditLogComponent

UI

Read-only table

Columns:

Timestamp

Actor (Admin ID)

Action

Target entity

Behavior

Pagination

Filter by action type

11. State Management Rules

No NgRx

Use:

signal() for local state

computed() for derived data

effect() for side effects

Use services with signals to share state between components

12. Component Input Rules

All component inputs must use:

readonly data = input<Type>();


No @Input()

No @Output(); use callback signals or services

13. UI Rules

Ionic components only (ion-card, ion-list, ion-button, etc.)

No direct DOM manipulation

No template-driven forms

14. Error Handling

Display form validation errors inline

Show Ionic alerts for critical errors

Disable actions while async operations are pending

15. Code Quality Constraints

One responsibility per component

No business logic in templates

Services handle API interaction only

All components must be standalone